definitions.definition: Something which or someone who impels .

subdefinitions.definition: A rotating component of a device that accelerates fluid , increasing its pressure or flowrate . Especially, such a component that drives the fluid radially (outward from a center of rotation) rather than axially . (Impellers are found in devices such as pumps, water jets, washing machines, and agitated tanks.)

main_definition: Something which or someone who impels .
